The Old Depot at Crow Jaw
[trigger settlement]

The woman scrubbing the depot floor doesn't look up when you enter. Her knuckles are swollen, her gray hair bound with clan-pattern cord. Behind her, a Kesharat patrol sergeant leans against a stack of rail ties, counting coins into his palm. "Found her hoarding water rations meant for the work crews," he says, addressing you without introduction. "Stealing from the Administration. Her son was supposed to pay restitution, settle the family debt." He drops the coins back into their purse with deliberate care. "He took the westbound rail three days ago instead."

The old woman's brush never stops moving across the floorboards. The depot is spotless already; has been for hours, you suspect. "My son owes nothing," she says to the floor. "This depot was clan waterhouse before your rails came. Before your decree-papers." Her voice carries the flatness of exhaustion. "He went to find work that pays. He'll send money."

The sergeant straightens. Your guild ring catches the light slanting through the depot door, and his expression shifts to something more calculating. "You're a person of standing. Commercial interests. You understand debt must be honored." He gestures at the woman. "The son abandoned his duty. Someone pays, or she works it off. Two years at depot maintenance, maybe three." His smile doesn't reach his eyes. "Unless someone of means wants to clear the account. Fifty eagles would settle it. The Lattice values those who restore proper order."

The old woman's brush finally stops. She looks at you for the first time, and her eyes are dry as the alkali flats.

choices:

* Move on = Not your concern
